attributes.logicalName: Credit Card Co Brand Regulatory Display Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the display codes to be used in regulatory report submissions for Credit Card Co Branch Type. 1. Co brand which typically related to products and services, including retail stores, airlines, etc. Excluding Oil and Gas cards, 2. Oil and Gas Co Brand, 3. Affinity which having affiliations such as Unions, Universities, etc. These cards typically do not offer rewards from these organizations, 4. Student if internally identified as a student card, 5. Other, 6. Health Care Card which is a card that can only be used specifically with the chosen medical providers and carry terms not typically available to general purpose cards or private label cards.
Refers to the co branding type or association code linked to the said credit card. Credit Card Co Brand Type Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

attributes.logicalName: Credit Card Co Brand Type Description
attributes.gcd: Refers to the co branding type or association descriptions linked to the said credit card. Credit Card Co Brand Type Dimension is the equivalent dimension table for this column.

attributes.logicalName: Credit Card Co Brand Type Numeric Identifier
attributes.gcd: Refers to the equivalent numeric identifier of the Credit Card Co Brand Type.
